cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a variant of dropout regularization for hierarchical mixture of experts, which is a type of neural network model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also experiments with image datasets (MNIST and CIFAR-10), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
